Ingredients:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl280\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0 \cf3 \outl0\strokewidth0 2 tablespoons sesame oil\
2 tablespoons canola or vegetable oil\
3/4 to 1 pound boneless skinless chicken breasts, diced\
1 1/2 cups frozen peas and diced carrots blend (straight from freezer is fine!)\
3 sliced green onions\
2 to 3 mined garlic cloves\
3 lightly beaten large eggs\
4 cups cooked rice *\
3 to 4 tablespoons soy sauce\
Salt and pepper to taste \outl0\strokewidth0 \
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \

\f0\b How to:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 1. In a large non-stick skillet or wok, add the oils and chicken, and cook over medium-high heat for\'a0about 3 to 5 minutes, ensuring all sides cook evenly. Remove chicken with a slotted spoon (allow oils and cooking juices from chicken to remain in skillet) and set aside.\
2. Add the peas, carrots, green onions, and cook for about 2 minutes, or until vegetables begin to soften. Stir every once in a while.\
3. Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute making sure not to burn the garlic.\
4. Push vegetables to one side of the skillet, add the eggs to the other side, and cook to scramble.\
5. Add the chicken back in, add the rice and evenly drizzle with soy sauce. Add salt and pepper, and stir to combine. Cook for about 2 minutes, or until chicken is reheated through.\
\
*For the rice, it\'92s best if it\'92s day-old, cold rice. You can cook the rice ahead of time and leave in the fridge overnight or cook the rice first and thinly layer it on a cookie sheet to cool in the freezer while you prep. 5 minute rice is good enough, but you can use any rice you wish.\
